{
  "texts": [
    "In this section, we briefly introduce the necessary concepts and formulate our target problem.",
    "❶ Personality Traits: Personality traits refer to enduring patterns of thoughts, feelings, and behaviors that distinguish individuals from one another.",
    "These traits are consistent over time and across situations, contributing to the uniqueness of each person.",
    "In the context of psychology, various models have been developed to classify and understand these traits.",
    "Two prominent models are the Myers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI) and the Enneagram of Personality.❷ The MBTI is based on Carl Jung's theory of psychological types [12] and categorizes personality into 16 distinct types across four dichotomies:• Extraversion / Introversion, which reflects the source and direction of an individual's energy expression."
  ]
}